Ronaldo, Messi, Xavi Competing for FIFA World Soccer’s Player of Year

-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 
2011-12-05T10:48:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/ronaldo-messi-xavi-competing-for-fifa-world-soccer-s-player-of-year.html
Real Madrid’s Cristiano Ronaldo and
 Lionel Messi  and Xavi of Barcelona are the finalists for world
soccer Player of the Year, FIFA said.  Brazil’s Marta, Homare Sawa of Japan and American Abby
Wambach are the finalists for the women’s award, the sport’s
governing body said today in an e-mailed statement.  Manchester United’s Alex Ferguson, Barcelona’s Josep
Guardiola and Real Madrid’s  Jose Mourinho  are the candidates for
men’s team manager of the year, while France’s Bruno Bini,
Japan’s Norio Sasaki and Sweden’s Pia Sundhage, the coach of the
U.S. team, are finalists for the manager of a women’s team.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  